{{Infobox library|name=McClelland Irish Library|logo=<!-- file name only (no Image: or File:) -->|logo_size=|logo_alt=|image=<!-- file name only (no Image: or File:) -->|image_size=|alt=|caption=|country=USA|type=[[Public library]]|scope=|established=2012|ref_legal_mandate=|location=[[Phoenix, Arizona]]|coordinates={{coord|33.461104|-112.074304|display=it}}|branch_of=|num_branches=|items_collected=|collection_size=6000|criteria=|legal_deposit=|req_to_access=|annual_circulation=|pop_served=|members=|budget=|director=|num_employees=|website={{URL|http://www.azirishlibrary.org/}}}} The '''McClelland Irish Library''' is a [[Library]] situated in and owned by the city of [[Phoenix, Arizona]] holding a collection of works related to [[Celts|Celtic]] culture and genealogy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.azirishlibrary.org/|title=McClelland Irish Library {{!}} Dedicated to Irish Culture|website=www.azirishlibrary.org|access-date=2016-06-16}}</ref> The building housing the library cost $5 million to build and is modeled after a [[Normans|Norman]] castle.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.irishcentral.com/news/5-million-mcclelland-irish-center-library-opens-in-phoenix-arizona-173020421-237532371.html|title=$5 million McClelland Irish Center library opens in Phoenix, Arizona&nbsp;— VIDEO|date=2012-10-07|website=IrishCentral.com|access-date=2016-06-16}}</ref> The library holds over 6000 books about Irish culture and a collection of [[genealogy]] resources, and operates in conjunction with [[Phoenix Public Library]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://arizona.newszap.com/northvalley/116983-115/irish-cultural-center-opens|title=Irish Cultural Center opens $5 million library in Phoenix|website=arizona.newszap.com|access-date=2016-06-16}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
