{{Infobox organization | name = Pakistan Association Dubai | native_name = | image = [[File:New Image of PAD.png|New Image of PAD]] | image_size = | alt = | caption = | abbreviation = PAD | formation = 1960s | purpose = Community association | headquarters = P.O. Box. 426 [[Oud Metha Road]], Street 11, [[Bur Dubai]] | location = [[Dubai]], [[United Arab Emirates]] | membership = [[Pakistanis in the United Arab Emirates|Pakistani community]] | leader_title = President | leader_name = Dr. Faisel Ikram<ref name="History"/> | leader_title2 = Vice President | leader_name2 = Muhammad Zaim<ref name="History"/> | leader_title3 = General Secretary | leader_name3 = Sohail Ashraf<ref name="History"/> | mission = "To transform Pakistan Association Dubai into a prestigious institution that will be a source of utmost pride for every Pakistani residing in the United Arab Emirates"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pad.ae/pad-mission/|work=Pakistan Association Dubai|title=PAD Mission|accessdate=24 November 2014}}</ref> | website = {{url|http://pad.ae/}} }}
The '''Pakistan Association Dubai''' ('''PAD''') is the largest community center for overseas Pakistanis in the world. It was founded in the late 1960s as a platform for advancing the social and cultural interests of Pakistani expatriates residing in [[Dubai]] and more broadly, the [[United Arab Emirates]].
==History== The Pakistani diaspora in the UAE is the third largest [[overseas Pakistani]] community, and also one of the oldest expatriate groups in the UAE. There are currently over 1.2 million [[Pakistanis in the United Arab Emirates]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thenational.ae/news/uae-news/politics/polling-booths-to-be-set-up-across-the-uae-so-pakistanis-can-vote|title=Polling booths to be set up across the UAE so Pakistanis can vote|work=The National|date=8 April 2013|accessdate=23 November 2014}}</ref> out of which over 400,000 are based in Dubai alone.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thenational.ae/news/uae-news/election-looms-for-pakistan-community-group|title=Election looms for Pakistan community group|work=The National|first=Nadeem|last=Hanif|date=8 May 2011|accessdate=23 November 2014}}</ref> Pakistanis collectively comprise around 13% of Dubai's population and are the third largest ethnic group in the emirate (after [[Indians in the United Arab Emirates|Indians]] and native [[Emirati people|Emiratis]]).<ref>{{cite book|last1=Jandt|first1=Fred E.|title=An Introduction to Intercultural Communication: Identities in a Global Community|date=2012|publisher=SAGE|isbn=9781452285757|page=237}}</ref> When PAD was founded in the late 1960s by members of the early community, it was initially based at a small rented office space in Murshid Bazar in [[Deira]], where the [[Pakistan Education Academy, Dubai|Pakistan Education Academy]] now exists.<ref name="History"/> By the early 1990s, the office was shifted to the Astoria Hotel in [[Bur Dubai]]. Later, the centre where the association is now headquartered was built on [[Oud Metha Road]] in Bur Dubai.<ref name="History"/> The objectives of PAD include promoting relations between Pakistan and the UAE, providing community support and welfare, promoting Pakistani culture, organising recreational community events, and enhancing the interests of the Pakistani expatriate community in the UAE.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pad.ae/pad-vision/|title=PAD Vision|work=Pakistan Association Dubai|accessdate=24 November 2014}}</ref>
==Structure== The association elects a president who formally heads the organisation, typically for a tenure of two to three years. A vice-president, general-secretary and joint-secretary are also elected as part of the executive body. Membership is required to register and participate in the association.<ref name="History">{{cite web|url=http://pad.ae/history/|title=History|work=Pakistan Association Dubai|accessdate=23 November 2014}}</ref> PAD works closely with the [[Consulate-General of Pakistan, Dubai|Consulate-General of Pakistan in Dubai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pakistanconsulate.ae/association.html|title=Pakistan Associations and Centres in Dubai and Northern Emirates|work=Consulate General of Pakistan, Dubai|accessdate=21 November 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141124102531/http://www.pakistanconsulate.ae/association.html|archivedate=24 November 2014|df=}}</ref> There are multiple community wings operating under PAD. These include the medical, engineering, journalist, professional, accounting and ladies wings, among others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pad.ae/wings/|title=Wings|work=Pakistan Association Dubai|accessdate=24 November 2014}}</ref>
==Events and activities== PAD arranges numerous cultural events and gatherings in the community, such as [[Independence Day (Pakistan)|Independence Day]], [[Pakistan Day]] and [[National Day (United Arab Emirates)|UAE National Day]] celebrations, literary events including [[mushaira]]s, [[iftar]] dinners during Ramadan, [[Chaand Raat|chaand raat]] events, [[Meena Bazaar|meena bazaar]]s, fundraising dinners and awareness events, award ceremonies, art exhibitions, sport and leisurely events, as well as workshops and language classes. PAD also arranges support services for Pakistanis in the [[Labour force of the United Arab Emirates|UAE labour force]], as well welfare activities both in Pakistan and the UAE.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pad.ae/category/news-feed/|title=News Feed|work=Pakistan Association Dubai|accessdate=24 November 2014}}</ref><ref name="Events">{{cite web|url=http://pad.ae/category/events/|title=Events|work=Pakistan Association Dubai|accessdate=24 November 2014}}</ref> A newsletter is published and distributed by the association.<ref name="Events"/>
